<br>
Dark bargainers<br>
Dread Guard Inner<br>
Dread Guard Outer<br>
<br>
Also, there is no difference in faction recieved with handing in G.lightstones v/s lightstones, just the concordance as reward.<br>
<br>
Personally, I'd advise against working on guard faction, since you will still be forced to travel Neriak invis due to the random NPC's on TheDead and Queen faction.  In the time it would take you to go from KOS to dub to guards, you could have made a level or two killing the wizys. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=waldenawildfyre>Waldena Wildfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 266<br> <font color=#333333>(5/5/01 5:12:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wine quest &amp; lightstone factions</span><hr size=1> Is there a way to do necro without killing guard even ifya have bad faction with guard?  I was thinking lev/swim over to necros house then summon companion pet there, but if the necro is right at the door like he is sometimes, I wont be able to summon my pet there.  Ive tried summoning my pet to the bridge to the necros house, but that will argo the guard sometimes depending on where he is. <p><table border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1">
