<br>
Still, they drop swords that sell for 11pp, and a FS that sells for 5pp.  The shield sells for 1.5pp, and the even drop up to 5pp in actual pp.<br>
<br>
your best lvl 49 fire pet can SOLO some of the guards, I saw it many times.  The DS is just more then the guards can deal with.  On a few of the harder guards, you will have to do like 2-3 pet heals.  Yes I said pet heals, it does help.  You cant nuke, they resist, and 4 heals is about 1/2 of the 49 fire pets total HP.<br>
<br>
Now here is the beautifull part....<br>
<br>
When I was there, I consisantly killed all 3 nobles, and the guard in the 10 min spawn.<br>
<br>
KS the pet on the nobles, nuke HARD.  The pet will finish at lots of HP, and you will have spent like 2 nukes on each noble.  Then use the pet's HP as your resource to kill the guard.  When you do this right, you will be killing all 4 of those mobs in the 10 min time and your exp is much better.  Plus you can recruit a newbie in the zone to sell your swords for you and split the plat.  11pp+5pp+4pp = lots of pp for each guard...<br>
<br>
The best exp I ever got in that zone was when I was doing a duo with a cleric.  I would nuke the crap out of nobles for the kill, and he would heal my pet well for the guards.  There are more guards near the cleric guild that you can pull if you in a duo.  A mage and a cleric can kill the 3 nobles, and easily like 3 more guards in the 10 min spawn time.<br>
<br>
Best exp I have ever seen post lvl 50... <p><center><img src="http://www.homestead.com/balandar/files/eandori.jpg" width=173
